<doc id="458534" wikidata="Q21493272" url="?curid=458534" title="Cramer (surname)">
<text>Cramer is an English surname and the Anglicized version of Dutch and Low German Kramer, or German Krämer (pronounced ). Both refer to the profession of traveling merchants in the Late Middle Ages. The meaning later changed to &quot;merchants trading with different, rather small things.

Notable people with the name include:
