<doc id="458709" wikidata="Q7239729" url="?curid=458709" title="Predual">
<text>In mathematics, the predual of an object &quot;D&quot; is an object &quot;P&quot; whose dual space is &quot;D&quot;.

For example, the predual of the space of bounded operators is the space of trace class operators, and the predual of the space &quot;L&quot;∞(R) of essentially bounded functions on R is the Banach space &quot;L&quot;1(R) of integrable functions.</text><links>
