<doc id="458729" wikidata="Q191872" url="?curid=458729" title="Bulqizë District">
<text>Bulqizë District () was one of the 36 districts of Albania, which were dissolved in July 2000 and replaced by 12 counties. It had a population of 42,985 in 2001, and an area of . Located in the east of the country, its capital was the town of Bulqizë. The area of the former district is with the present municipality of Bulqizë, which is part of Dibër County.

==Administrative divisions==
The district consisted of the following municipalities:

*Bulqizë
*Fushë-Bulqizë
*Gjoricë
*Martanesh
*Ostren
*Shupenzë
*Trebisht
*Zerqan

