<doc id="458732" wikidata="Q166959" url="?curid=458732" title="Delvinë District">
<text>Delvinë District (Albanian: &quot;Rrethi i Delvinës&quot;) was one of the 36 districts of Albania, which were dissolved in July 2000 and replaced by 12 counties. It had a population of 10,859 in 2001, and an area of . Its population included a substantial Greek community. The district is in the south of the country, and its capital was the town of Delvinë. Its territory is now part of Vlorë County: the municipalities of Delvinë and Finiq (partly).

==Administrative divisions==
The district consisted of the following municipalities:

*Delvinë
*Vergo
*Finiq
*Mesopotam

