<doc id="458736" wikidata="Q192123" url="?curid=458736" title="Dibër District">
<text>Dibër District () was one of the 36 districts of Albania, which were dissolved in July 2000 and replaced by 12 counties. It had a population of 86,144 in 2001, and an area of . Located in the northeast of the country, its capital was Peshkopi. The area of the former district is with the present municipality of Dibër, which is part of Dibër County.

==Administrative divisions==
The district consisted of the following municipalities:

*Arras
*Fushë-Çidhën
*Kala e Dodës
*Kastriot
*Lurë
*Luzni
*Maqellarë
*Melan
*Muhurr
*Peshkopi
*Qendër Tomin
*Selishtë
*Sllovë
*Zall-Dardhë
*Zall-Reç

==Notable people==
*Skanderbeg
*Gjon Kastrioti
*Fiqri Dine

